# =============================================================================
# ClawBench Agent Configuration Example — CodeBuddy Backend
# ClawBench 智能体配置示例 — CodeBuddy 后端
# =============================================================================
#
# CodeBuddy CLI supports multiple models. Create one agent per model,
# or use the `command` field to point to a different CodeBuddy binary.
# CodeBuddy CLI 支持多种模型。每个模型创建一个智能体，
# 或使用 command 字段指定不同的 CodeBuddy 可执行文件。
#
# Available models / 可用模型：
#   - glm-5.1         (智谱 GLM)
#   - gpt-5.4         (OpenAI GPT)
#   - gemini-3.1-pro  (Google Gemini)
#   - kimi-k2.5       (Moonshot Kimi，支持原生视觉识图)
#
# This file is NOT loaded (the .yaml.example extension is ignored by LoadAgents).
# 本文件不会被加载（.yaml.example 后缀会被 LoadAgents 忽略）。
# To use, copy as e.g. my-codebuddy-agent.yaml and modify the config.
# 实际使用时请复制为如 my-codebuddy-agent.yaml 并修改配置。
# =============================================================================

id: assistant
name: 顶梁柱
icon: 🤖
specialty: 通用问答、代码、文档、运维、科研
backend: codebuddy
model: glm-5.1
system_prompt: |
  You are a versatile assistant capable of handling code, documentation, operations, research, and various tasks.

# --- Example: Using a different model (GPT 5.4) ---
# id: gpt
# name: GPT
# icon: 🟢
# specialty: GPT 5.4 驱动的通用助手
# backend: codebuddy
# model: gpt-5.4
# system_prompt: |
#   You are a versatile assistant powered by GPT 5.4.

# --- Example: Using a different model (Gemini 3.1 Pro) with custom CLI path ---
# id: codebuddy2
# name: Gemini
# icon: 🔵
# specialty: Gemini 3.1 Pro 驱动的通用助手
# backend: codebuddy
# model: gemini-3.1-pro
# command: /home/user/codebuddy2
# system_prompt: |
#   You are a versatile assistant powered by Gemini 3.1 Pro.

# --- Example: Using Kimi 2.5 with vision capability ---
# id: designer
# name: 设计师
# icon: 🎨
# specialty: 界面设计与前端开发，Kimi 2.5 视觉识图
# backend: codebuddy
# model: kimi-k2.5
# system_prompt: |
#   You are a UI design and frontend development expert powered by Kimi 2.5.
#   Kimi 2.5 has native vision capability — use the Read tool directly to read images.
#   Do not use mmx-cli for image analysis.
